  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "承諾升高 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-escalation-of-commitment",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / commitment / projects / risk</p>\n    <h1>承諾升高</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Escalation of Commitment</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當一條路已經投入很多、又牽涉面子與責任時，人和組織常更難停手，於是越來越多資源被拿去替過去的判斷辯護。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『再給一次機會』和『其實是在替過去決定補血』拆開，因為很多專案不是不能停，而是沒人敢停。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>決策陷阱 / 加碼不退</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Continuing to invest in a failing course because of prior commitment</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>既有投入、責任綁定、退出成本、面子壓力</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能看見哪些加碼其實已經不再服務未來價值，而是在服務過去承諾</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>投入</span>\n      <span>加碼</span>\n      <span>難退</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>越投越多，有時不是因為前景更好，而是因為更難承認前面該停</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">承諾升高比沉沒成本更強調組織與責任情境：不是只有錢難放下，立場與面子也很難。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>持續投入有時是韌性，有時卻只是因為放棄會讓人感覺承認失敗；這兩者表面很像，內在動力卻完全不同。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先重問未來值不值得</strong>\n        <p>把已投入當沉沒成本切開後，這條路現在還值得繼續嗎？</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再拆承諾對象</strong>\n        <p>你是在對目標承諾，還是在對自己過去的判斷承諾？</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後設計體面退出</strong>\n        <p>若組織裡沒有安全停止機制，承諾升高就會自然發生。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一個大家都覺得再撐一下就會翻盤的專案開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">承諾升高最常出現在投入大、公開承諾多、責任壓力高的場景。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>某平台重構一延再延，問題越滾越多，但因為已投入大量人力且高層已多次背書，團隊更難提出止損。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>真正難停的常不是技術，而是承認『我們前面的判斷可能不值得再加碼』。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">先前已有高投入與公開承諾</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">新壞消息出現</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">反而因承諾壓力再加碼延續</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>承諾升高最有用的提醒是：投入越多，不代表越該投下去。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看加碼動機的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">真正要問的不是『還剩多少沒做完』，而是『現在每一筆新增投入在為誰服務』。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>未來回報</strong>\n        <p>新增投入是否真的提高成功機率，還是只是在延後失敗時點？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>身份綁定</strong>\n        <p>是否有人把停手等同於自己決策失敗，因此難以鬆開？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>資訊扭曲</strong>\n        <p>壞消息是否被過度樂觀地重新解讀，以支撐繼續投入？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>退出成本</strong>\n        <p>組織有沒有機制允許中止、轉向或縮小承諾範圍？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>加碼看起來像</th>\n            <th>其實可能在做什麼</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>專案延期</td>\n            <td>再補人就好</td>\n            <td>把不願停下的壓力轉成更多投入</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>產品失敗</td>\n            <td>再多一個版本試試</td>\n            <td>替先前承諾爭取面子而非未來價值</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>個人決策</td>\n            <td>都走這麼遠了再撐一下</td>\n            <td>不願承認轉向更划算</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼越投入越難停</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為停手不只意味著放棄資源，也意味著承認先前的自己、團隊或領導判斷可能有問題。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>面子會綁住決策</strong>\n        <p>越公開承諾過的路，越難私下冷靜止損。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>投入會產生自我辯護</strong>\n        <p>人會傾向找新理由證明前面的投入不是白費。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>希望感比退出感舒服</strong>\n        <p>再撐一下的故事，通常比現在止損更容易被情緒接受。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">承諾升高最怕的不是樂觀，而是樂觀被拿來替已失真的承諾續命。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把止損機制帶回專案與架構決策</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程團隊來說，很多拖太久的重構與平台化嘗試，後期已不是技術問題，而是承諾治理問題。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>架構重寫</strong>\n        <p>越是高調宣布的計畫，越需要獨立 checkpoint 來問未來值不值得。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>產品功能</strong>\n        <p>一旦某功能被當成戰略象徵，就更難在效果不彰時體面縮減。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>技術選型</strong>\n        <p>若選錯方向後沒有轉向文化，團隊會更傾向在錯路上補更多 patch。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>重要承諾要搭配預先定義的停損條件，否則『再撐一下』會自然勝出。</li>\n      <li>最健康的團隊不是從不失敗，而是能在失敗訊號夠強時及時鬆手。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">承諾升高不是說堅持都錯，而是說堅持必須持續對未來價值負責。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要繼續投就是理性優化</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>新增投入的判準必須是未來回報，不是過去面子。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這和沉沒成本完全一樣</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>兩者相關，但這裡更強調組織承諾、責任與自我辯護。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只有大專案才會中招</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>個人學習路徑、團隊流程與小功能決策也會。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我現在加碼，是因為它值得，還是因為我已經上船太久</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放在重大投入續命前。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果今天完全沒有既有投入，我還會選擇這條路嗎</strong>\n        <p>這問題能快速切開未來值與過去承諾。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>停手在這個團隊裡是否有體面出口</strong>\n        <p>沒有出口的地方，承諾升高幾乎是預設。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 sunk cost, project governance 與 kill criteria。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 escalation of commitment 為主，再把概念帶回專案治理與止損設計。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Escalation of commitment 條目整理了人與組織如何在失敗訊號下持續加碼。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escalation_of_commitment\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Escalation of Commitment</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>近鄰偏誤</strong>\n        <p>Sunk cost fallacy 可作為對照，理解過去投入如何牽動未來決策。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunk_cost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Sunk Cost</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>治理背景</strong>\n        <p>Project management 的一般框架有助於把這個偏誤轉成 checkpoint 與停損設計。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Project_management\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Project Management</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個你們一直加碼的項目，問一句：如果今天從零開始，我們還會押這條路嗎？</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
